</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="694" pageNumber="695" type="note">
<paragraph pageId="694" pageNumber="695">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="694" pageNumber="695">
This species is externally very similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mannerheim" authorityYear="1853" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="694" pageNumber="695" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulvilabris">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="694" pageNumber="695">Harpalus fulvilabris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and Lindroth (1968: 783) included these two species in one species group. However, Noonan (1991) listed the two species in different species groups suggesting that the similarities are probably due to convergent evolution.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
